  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nIt may be the purist in me but \r\n```\r\n000000: PUSH1 0x60\r\n000002: PUSH1 0x40\r\n000004: MSTORE\r\n000005: CALLVALUE\r\n000006: ISZERO\r\n000007: PUSH3 0x000010\r\n000011: JUMPI\r\n000012: PUSH1 0x00\r\n000014: DUP1\r\n000015: REVERT\r\n000016: JUMPDEST\r\n000017: PUSH1 0x40\r\n000019: MLOAD\r\n000020: PUSH1 0x20\r\n000022: DUP1\r\n```\r\nwould look so much better as \r\n```\r\n000000: PUSH1 0x60\r\n000002: PUSH1 0x40\r\n000004: MSTORE\r\n000005: CALLVALUE\r\n000006: ISZERO\r\n000007: PUSH3 0x000010\r\n00000B: JUMPI\r\n00000C: PUSH1 0x00\r\n00000E: DUP1\r\n00000F: REVERT\r\n000010: JUMPDEST\r\n000011: PUSH1 0x40\r\n000013: MLOAD\r\n000014: PUSH1 0x20\r\n000016: DUP1\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf evm.PrintDisassembled isn't used anywhere else, any objection to making it hex or at least having a hex address option?\r\n\r\nIf OK - I will do it and submit it.",
